    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Wash, then chop the <strong>roots</strong> from your <strong>pak choi</strong> and separate the leaves, discarding the roots</p><p>Chop any <strong>larger leaves</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sea-bass-with-pak-choi-and-szechuan-style-noodles/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>medium</strong> <strong>egg noodles</strong> and <strong>pak choi </strong>to a pot and cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong> until they're fully submerged</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until the noodles are cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and set aside</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sea-bass-with-pak-choi-and-szechuan-style-noodles/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Pat your<strong> sea bass fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season the skin with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, once hot, add the <strong>sea bass</strong>, skin side down and cook for 6 min, then flip the sea bass and cook for 1 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Transfer the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>sea bass </strong>to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sea-bass-with-pak-choi-and-szechuan-style-noodles/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sea-bass-with-pak-choi-and-szechuan-style-noodles/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>in a measuring jug and mix until fully combined</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sea-bass-with-pak-choi-and-szechuan-style-noodles/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>honey</strong>,<strong> soy sauce</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar </strong>to the measuring jug and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>Szechuan-style sauce</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>Szechuan-style sauce </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 1-2 minutes or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sea-bass-with-pak-choi-and-szechuan-style-noodles/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once your sauce has thickened, add the <strong>drained noodles </strong>to the pan with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and the <strong>wilted pak choi</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further or until the noodles and pak choi are warmed through</p><p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> pepper </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>Szechuan-style noodles</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sea-bass-with-pak-choi-and-szechuan-style-noodles/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Szechuan-style noodles</strong> with the <strong>sea bass</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sea-bass-with-pak-choi-and-szechuan-style-noodles/step-8.jpg"
        }
    ],
